    "Applied Learning\nApplied Learning for industry readiness\nOur pedagogy focuses on the application of learning into actual industry contexts.\nAACSB Business Education Alliance: As part of this prestigious alliance, we gain access to cutting-edge research, international collaborations, best practices in curriculum innovation, and a global community of business educators and industry leaders. This membership reinforces our commitment to delivering high-quality, relevant, and globally connected business education that prepares our students for success in a dynamic world. Being part of the AACSB community helps us stay at the forefront of business education and continuously enhance the learning experience for our students.\nExplore BCD Programmes\nLearn about the current programmes offered under the BCD cluster.\nUndergraduate\nSIT\nAccountancy\n3 years\n.\n180 credits\nSIT\nAviation Management\n3 years\n.\n180 credits\nSIT\nBusiness and Infocomm Technology\n4 years\n.\n240 credits\nSIT\nCommunication and Digital Media\n3 years\n.\n180 credits\nThe Culinary Institute of America\nFood Business Management (Baking and Pastry Arts)\n2 years\n.\n132 credits\nThe Culinary Institute of America\nFood Business Management (Culinary Arts)\n2 years\n.\n132 credits\nSIT\nHospitality and Tourism Management\n3 years\n.\n180 credits\nchevron--up\nMinors\nMinor in Data Analytics and Digital Transformation (MDD)"
